SIMPLE: infernal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infernal
<hw>In*fer"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>infernal</ets>, L. <ets>infernalis</ets>, fr. <ets>infernus</ets>
that which lies beneath, the lower. See <er>Inferior</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to or suitable for the lower
regions, inhabited, according to the ancients, by the dead; pertaining
to Pluto's realm of the dead, the Tartarus of the ancients.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Elysian fields, the <qex>infernal</qex> monarchy.</q>
<rj><qau>Garth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to, resembling, or inhabiting,
hell; suitable for hell, or to the character of the inhabitants of hell;
hellish; diabolical; <as>as, <ex>infernal</ex> spirits, or
conduct</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The instruments or abettors in such <qex>infernal</qex>
dealings.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Infernal machine</b></col>, <cd>a machine or apparatus
maliciously designed to explode, and destroy life or property.</cd> --
<col><b>Infernal stone</b></col> <cd>(<altname>lapis
infernalis</altname>), lunar caustic; formerly so called. The name was
also applied to caustic potash.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Tartarean; Stygian; hellish; devilish;
diabolical; satanic; fiendish; malicious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infernal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infernal
<hw>In*fer"nal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An inhabitant of the infernal
regions; also, the place itself.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infernally</ent>⟦br⟧
